THE LEARNING STATION is a multi-award-winning children's group. With combined backgrounds and degrees in early childhood education, child development and music, this trio, has achieved international stature as leaders in the children's educational music industry. "Ba Ba Bones"
From the CD and DVD, "Physical Ed"
©Monopoli/The Learning Station

Action: Touch the part of the body the lyrics refer to and sing along with verses and choruses. 

"Sometimes you find small bones while you're digging. Sometimes you see big bones all connected in a museum, or sometimes by themselves. The reason why we're singing about bones is because that's the framework that keeps us together. That's why we stand straight and tall and proud and that's why we sing this song." The toe bone's connected to the foot bone. The foot bone's connected to the ankle bone. The ankle bone's connected to the shin bone. The shin bone's connected to the knee bone. 

Chorus: We got so many parts and so many sections. We need the bones to make the connections. Ba, ba, ba, ba, ba, ba, ba, bones. ( Ba, ba, ba, ba, ba, ba, ba, bones.) 2xWe got so many parts and so many sections. We need the bones to make the connections. The knee bone's connected to the thigh bone. The thigh bone's connected to the hip bone. The hip bone's connected to the back bone. The back bone's connected to the chest bones. Repeat Chorus

The chest bone's connected to the shoulder bone. The shoulder bone's connected to the arm bone. The arm bone's connected to the wrist bone. The wrist bone's connected to the hand bone. 

Repeat Chorus The neck bone's connected to the head bone. The head bone's connected to the nose bone. (That's cartilage!) Well, how about the ear bone. (That's cartilage too!) "We have more parts than I thought!" Repeat Chorus 

"That's right, you got to keep your bones real healthy and real strong. You got to make sure you get enough calcium because that's the framework of your body to stay real healthy. Keep your teeth real strong and healthy too."

Hey everybody. So, we are going to break down the wobble dance today and if you have ever been to a BBQ, a wedding or a cruise, you will hear this, you will see this dance, you will hear this song on constant rotation about every 10 minutes. People love it. It is the new electric slide. We are going to break this down. The magic numbers are one and five. Just remember that. 

One, you are going to jump forward. Boom. Easy. Ok. Lets try that again. So we have, 5,6,7,8, jump 1. Now, when you jump here you are just going to groove, body roll, do whatever you kind of like. Any salt and pepper, onion, garlic flavor you got. So, you are going to go, 1,2,3,4, jump 5,6,7,8. 

Next part, just lean to the right, step out to the right with your right foot. Everything with the right foot. For you, it is going to look like left, for me it is my right. 5,6,7,8,1,2,3,4, other side, 5,6,7,8. Good, lets take that a little slower. So, we just jump back. 5,6,7,8, jumping out to the right. 1,2,3,4, to the left, 5,6,7,8. You have to groove, you always have to groove. You can use a little salt. So, you go 1,2,3,4,5,6,7,8. Repeat. 1,2,3,4,5,6,7,8. 

Now, for the sauce. Some people will go up, up and cha cha cha. Up, up and cha cha cha. We are going to try mixing them up a little bit together. So, we will go up, 2, back 3, 4, now up 6 and cha cha cha. 

Now, lets try this with some music. I think you got it. [Music Plays] So, get your groove first. You want to be ready. You do not what to just start dancing from here. 5,6,7,8. 

There you have it. Through your own little flavor in it. Have a little fun. There is no limit to what you can do with the wobble dance.

It gets a little complicated somewhere in there, but it gets fun. Check out the feet. All right, so what's going to happen is your right foot is going to be on the heel and you turn it out and then the left foot is going to be on the toe, and you turn that heel in. 

So, basically, both heels come forward, right? So when they start back again, the right foot is on the heel and the left foot is on the toe. In your mind you're thinking heel, toe, but this is a lot different than that. This is The Happy Feet, right? 

So, you're going to turn your right foot, it's going to be on the heel and you turn the toe out. Then you turn the left foot, which is going to be on the toe, you turn that heel in. So both heels come forward and you have one going out and one going in. That's what it looks like when you're standing still. It looks like this, six, seven, eight, hit, bring it back down and then you go the other way, the complete opposite of what you did before. Go. 

Now, bring it back down. Now, let's explain the other side. So, hit it and hold it. You have your left on your heel, the left went out, the right on the toe, and that came in. Again, you have both of your heels forward. Got it? Bring it down.

"Now from the top, make it drop, that's so wet that's so wet
Now get a bucket and a mop, that's so wet that's so wet
I'm talkin' wap, wap, wap, that's so wet that's so wet
Macaroni in a pot, that's so wet that's so wet"

I'm so happy that this WAP dance is done to a "clean" part, or else I probably wouldn't have made this tutorial 😜
